  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\npause does not reap zombie processes using the default pause container provided by gcr.io/google_containers/pause-amd64:3.0\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\ngcr.io/google_containers/pause-amd64:3.0 should include the up to date pause code to reap zombie processes when using docker >= 1.13.1 found here\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/build/pause/pause.c\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n```\r\nkubectl create -f https://k8s.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/shell-demo.yaml\r\nkubectl exec -it shell-demo -- /bin/bash\r\n# apt update\r\n# apt install curl gcc procps\r\n# curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/master/build/pause/orphan.c\r\n# gcc orphan.c\r\n# ./a.out\r\n# ps ax\r\n```\r\na.out will leave a zombie process that is not cleaned up\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nBuilding the pause container from master solves this issue\r\n\r\nRelated:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/45236\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/36853\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/1615\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.7.0+\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: N/A\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): CentOS 7\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):  4.10.13+\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others: docker >= 1.13.1\r\n",
